result.execSummary:
Jordan R Jacobs was extradited to another county, state or jurisdiction. Extradition means Jordan R Jacobs was accused or convicted of an offense in another county, state or jurisdiction and was taken there to face their charge(s) or conviction.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.
result.caption: State of Wisconsin vs. Jordan R Jacobs

records.addlTxt: Defendant picked up by McHenry Co IL.
Warrant for Commitment, signed by CC Rieck on 10/17/2022.
Defendant to comply with I.D. Processing.

1:34 PM District Attorney's Office Law Intern appeared for the State of Wisconsin by Jack Rieder and ADA Alyssa Jay. Defendant Jordan R Jacobs in court, in custody.  Attorney J Andrew Herbers Jr. in court for Jordan R Jacobs. 

Defense acknowledges receipt of complaint and waives reading. 
State of Illinois is requesting extradition for Theft (over $500.00).
Court Conducts Waiver of Extradition Colloquy with the defendant.
Defendant waives their right to extradition.
Court accepts the waiver of extradition.
Parties and the court sign the waiver of extradition and Court Commissioner signs the Order for Commitment.

The State gives its bail recommendation.
Defense gives its bail recommendation.

BOND:
The Court sets cash bail in the amount of $50,000.00.  

State of Illinois is to be notified ASAP that the defendant is available for pick up.
Court sets matter for a review hearing to ensure the defendant was picked up.
Hearing scheduled for November 16, 2022 at 08:30 am.
